HEADWORD: Ramist
<hw>Ra"mist</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧"m⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
follower of <person>Pierre <etsep>Ram⟦eacute⟧</etsep></person>, better
known as <person><it>Ramus</it></person>, a celebrated French scholar,
who was professor of rhetoric and philosophy at Paris in the reign of
<person>Henry II.</person>, and opposed the Aristotelians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

